 very common), but also because it's just<br />not that legible.<br /><br />I've argued several times that we shouldn't use the defines at all.<br />The octal format isn't any less legible than any #define I've ever<br />seen, and is generally _more_ legible.<br /><br />What's wrong with just using 0400 for "read by user"?<br /><br />                Linus<br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
